# Social Login API Testing Guide

## Base URL

```
http://localhost:5000/api/v1

 ```

## Endpoint

POST `/auth/login/social`

## Testing Google Login

### Request Headers

```
Content-Type: application/json

 ```

### Google Login Request Body

``` json
{
  "email": "user@gmail.com",
  "name": "Google User",
  "type": "GOOGLE",
  "fcmToken": "firebase_cloud_messaging_token_here",
  "role": "USER",
  "image": "https://example.com/profile.jpg"
}

 ```

### Test Cases for Google Login

1. {"email": "newuser@gmail.com","name": "New Google User","type": "GOOGLE","fcmToken": "fcm_token_123","role": "USER","image": "https://example.com/profile.jpg"}

2. {"email": "host@gmail.com","name": "Host Google User","type": "GOOGLE","fcmToken": "fcm_token_456","role": "HOST","image": "https://example.com/host.jpg"}

3. {"email": "fail@gmail.com","name": "Fail Test","type": "GOOGLE","role": "USER"}


## Testing Apple Login

### Apple Login Request Body

``` json
{
  "email": "user@icloud.com",
  "name": "Apple User",
  "type": "APPLE",
  "appId": "apple_unique_id_here",
  "role": "USER",
  "image": "https://example.com/profile.jpg"
}

 ```

### Test Cases for Apple Login

1. {"email": "newuser@icloud.com","name": "New Apple User","type": "APPLE","appId": "apple_id_123","role": "USER","image": "https://example.com/profile.jpg"}

2. {"email": "host@icloud.com","name": "Host Apple User","type": "APPLE","appId": "apple_id_456","role": "HOST","image": "https://example.com/host.jpg"}

3. {"email": "fail@icloud.com","name": "Fail Test","type": "APPLE","role": "USER"}


## Expected Responses

### Success Response (200 OK)

``` json
{
  "success": true,
  "statusCode": 200,
  "message": "User logged in successfully",
  "data": {
    "accessToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1...",
    "refreshToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1...",
    "user": {
      "id": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
      "name": "Test User",
      "email": "test@example.com",
      "role": "USER",
      "image": "https://example.com/profile.jpg",
      "verified": true,
      "status": "active",
      "loginType": "GOOGLE" // or "APPLE"
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Error Responses

1. {"success": false,"statusCode": 400,"message": "FCM token is required for Google login","errorMessages": \[ { "path": "fcmToken", "message": "FCM token is required for Google login" }\]}


## Postman Environment Setup

Create a new environment with these variables:

```
BASE_URL: http://localhost:5000/api/v1
ACCESS_TOKEN: <empty>
REFRESH_TOKEN: <empty>

 ```

## Postman Test Script

``` javascript
// Add this to the Tests tab
const response = pm.response.json();
if (response.data && response.data.accessToken) {
    pm.environment.set('ACCESS_TOKEN', response.data.accessToken);
    pm.environment.set('REFRESH_TOKEN', response.data.refreshToken);
}
// Add basic validation
pm.test("Status code is 200", function () {
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});
pm.test("Response has required fields", function () {
    pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property('accessToken');
    pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property('refreshToken');
    pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property('user');
});

 ```

