item.description:
# Card Payment API Documentation

## Base URL

```
{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/cards

 ```

## Environment Variables Setup

Create these variables in your Postman environment:

- `baseUrl`: Your API base URL (e.g., [http://localhost:5000](http://localhost:5000))

- `authToken`: JWT token for authentication


## Authentication

All endpoints require authentication. Add this to your request headers:

```
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

 ```

## API Endpoints

### 1\. Add New Card

**Endpoint:** POST `/add`

**Request Body:**

``` json
{
    "cardHolderName": "John Doe",
    "cardNumber": "4532015112830366",
    "cardType": "visa",
    "expiryDate": "12/25",
    "cvv": "123",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "phone": "+1234567890",
    "isDefault": true
}

 ```

**Test Cases:**

1. pm.test("Should successfully add a new card", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.equal("Card added successfully"); pm.expect(pm.response.json().data).to.have.property("lastFourDigits");});

2. { "cardHolderName": "John Doe", "cardNumber": "4532015112830367", // Invalid checksum "cardType": "visa", "expiryDate": "12/25", "cvv": "123", "email": "john.doe@example.com", "phone": "+1234567890"}

3. { "cardHolderName": "John Doe", "cardNumber": "4532015112830366", "cardType": "visa", "expiryDate": "12/22", // Expired date "cvv": "123", "email": "john.doe@example.com", "phone": "+1234567890"}


### 2\. Get All Cards

**Endpoint:** GET `/`

**Test Cases:**

1. pm.test("Should retrieve all cards", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; pm.expect(pm.response.json().data).to.be.an('array');});

2. pm.test("Card data should have required properties", function () { const card = pm.response.json().data\[0\]; pm.expect(card).to.have.property('cardHolderName'); pm.expect(card).to.have.property('lastFourDigits'); pm.expect(card).to.not.have.property('cardNumber'); pm.expect(card).to.not.have.property('cvv');});


### 3\. Get Card by ID

**Endpoint:** GET `/:cardId`

**Test Cases:**

1. pm.test("Should retrieve specific card", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); pm.expect(pm.response.json().data._id).to.equal(pm.variables.get("cardId"));});

2. // Use non-existent card IDpm.test("Should return 404 for non-existent card", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(404); pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.equal("Card not found");});


### 4\. Update Card

**Endpoint:** PATCH `/:cardId`

**Request Body:**

``` json
{
    "cardHolderName": "John Smith",
    "expiryDate": "12/26",
    "email": "john.smith@example.com",
    "phone": "+1987654321"
}

 ```

**Test Cases:**

1. pm.test("Should update card successfully", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); pm.expect(pm.response.json().data.cardHolderName).to.equal("John Smith");});

2. { "expiryDate": "13/26" // Invalid month}


### 5\. Delete Card

**Endpoint:** DELETE `/:cardId`

**Test Cases:**

1. pm.test("Should delete card successfully", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.equal("Card deleted successfully");});

2. // Follow-up GET request to verify card is deletedpm.test("Card should not exist after deletion", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(404);});


### 6\. Set Default Card

**Endpoint:** PATCH `/:cardId/set-default`

**Test Cases:**

1. pm.test("Should set card as default", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); pm.expect(pm.response.json().data.isDefault).to.be.true;});

2. // In the GET all cards requestpm.test("Only one card should be default", function () { const cards = pm.response.json().data; const defaultCards = cards.filter(card => card.isDefault); pm.expect(defaultCards.length).to.equal(1);});


## Test Data Sets

### Valid Test Cards

1. { "cardNumber": "4532015112830366", "cardType": "visa"}

2. { "cardNumber": "5425233430109903", "cardType": "mastercard"}


### Invalid Test Cards

1. { "cardNumber": "4532015112830366", "cardType": "mastercard" // Visa number with Mastercard type}

2. { "cardNumber": "4532015112830367"}


## Postman Collection Setup

1. Create a new collection named "Card Payment API"

2. Set up environment variables

3. if (!pm.environment.get('authToken')) { console.error('Authentication token not found in environment');}

4. pm.test("Response time is acceptable", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(1000);});

5. pm.test("Response should be JSON", function () { pm.response.to.be.json;});


pm.test("Response structure is correct", function () {  
pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('success');  
pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('message');  
if (pm.response.json().success) {  
pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('data');  
}  
});  
\`\`\`

